; ******************************************************************************
; *                                                                            *
; *                          TEST NEW CLOTHING SYSTEM                          *
; *                                                                            *
; ******************************************************************************
; This script is designed to test the development of the new clothing system,
; which doesn't use the 'worn' entity any more to store clothes worn by Hero.
north
; ==============================================================================
; CLOTHING INITIALIZATION
; ==============================================================================
; Let's check that clothes have been properly initialized by the library.
; In the source adventure, worn items are places IN the wearing actor and set as
; 'IS donned', the library then takes care of adding them to the 'wearing' set.
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; HERO'S CLOTHING -> OK!
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
inventory
DBG sneakers
DBG boxers
DBG socks
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; NPC CLOTHING  -> OK!
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
examine assistant
DBG boots
DBG uniform
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; NESTED CLOTHING AND OBJECTS -> OK!
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Let's check that clothing items inside worn clothes are seen as being just
; carried, not worn. Previously the library would mark as 'donned' any object
; inside a worn item.
examine khakis
DBG khakis
; The kippah shouldn't be 'donned' nor in 'wearing' of Hero:
DBG kippah
; ==============================================================================
; CLOTHES LISTINGS: HERO 
; ==============================================================================
; Now taking inventory shows two separate lists for carried and worn items.
; 
; ** NOTE ** ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
;            This is achieved via two custom loops (no LIST used) and only
;            checking if carried items are 'clothing' and 'donned'.
;            (no use of 'wearing' set)
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; HERO INVENTORY -> Empty handed + Wears many clothes
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; If Hero is not carrying anything, should report "empty-handed" message:
inventory
; ** NOTE ** ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
;            "empty-handed" would be better without hyphen!
;            ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
take wallet
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; HERO INVENTORY -> Carries one item + Wears many clothes
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Check correct handling of single item (no "," nor "and"):
inventory
north
put dungarees in basket
take basket
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; HERO INVENTORY -> Carries two item + Wears many clothes
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Check correct reporting using "and" between two items:
inventory
take skirt
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; HERO INVENTORY -> Carries many item + Wears many clothes
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Check that multiple items are comma separated except last ("and"):
inventory
take chair
inventory
; ** NOTE ** Using 'drop' here until 'remove' is fixed!
drop sneakers
drop khakis
drop undershirt
drop chair
drop basket
drop skirt
drop wallet
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; HERO INVENTORY -> Empty handed + Wears two clothes
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Check that the 2 worn items are "and" separated:
inventory
drop socks
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; HERO INVENTORY -> Empty handed + Wears one clothing
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Check that single worn item is followed by "." (no "," or "and"):
inventory
drop boxers
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; HERO INVENTORY -> Empty handed + Wears nothing
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
inventory
; ** NOTE ** ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
;            When the Hero is wearing nothing it might be best not to mention
;            "You are not wearing anything" because in games that won't be using
;            clothing it would be a useless messages. Not mentioning worn items
;            should be enough.
;            ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
; ==============================================================================
; CLOTHES LISTINGS: NPC -> OK!
; ==============================================================================
; Examining actors also prints two separate lists for carried and worn items.
; The system used is the same as for 'inventory', via custom loops and 'donned'.
take wallet
take skirt
take sneakers
south
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; NPC EXAMINE -> Carries one item + Wears 2 clothes
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
examine assistant
ask assistant for list
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; NPC EXAMINE -> Empty handed + Wears 2 clothes
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
examine assistant
give list to assistant
examine assistant
give wallet to assistant
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; NPC EXAMINE -> Carries 2 items + Wears 2 clothes
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
examine assistant
give skirt to assistant
examine assistant
give sneakers to assistant
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; NPC EXAMINE -> Carries many items + Wears 2 clothes
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
examine assistant
ask assistant for list
ask assistant for wallet
ask assistant for skirt
ask assistant for sneakers
ask assistant for boots
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; NPC EXAMINE -> Empty handed + Wears 1 clothes
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
examine assistant
ask assistant for uniform
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; NPC EXAMINE -> Empty handed + Wears nothing
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
examine assistant
